\f0\b \cf2 ## 3. Dev startup sequence (with local Redis + Cloud SQL dev)
\f1\b0 \cf0 \
\
From a clean reboot:\
\
### Terminal A \'96 Cloud SQL proxy (for `nexus_db`)\
\
```bash\
cloud-sql-proxy <INSTANCE_CONNECTION_NAME_FOR_nexusdev-v2> \\\
  --port=5434 \\\
  --address=127.0.0.1\
```\
- `<INSTANCE_CONNECTION_NAME_FOR_nexusdev-v2>` is the exact string from Cloud SQL \'93Instance connection name\'94.\
- Leave this window open.\
\
### Terminal B \'96 API (uses Cloud SQL + local Redis)\
\
```bash\
cd ~/nexus-enterprise\
npm run dev:api\
```\
- Uses `DATABASE_URL=...5434/nexus_db`.\
- Uses `REDIS_URL=redis://localhost:6379`.\
\
### Terminal C \'96 Worker (for background imports)\
\
```bash\
cd ~/nexus-enterprise/apps/api\
npm run worker:dev\
```\
- Connects to the same DB + Redis.\
- Processes `ImportJob` queue (`import-jobs`).\
\
### Terminal D \'96 Web app\
\
```bash\
cd ~/nexus-enterprise\
npm run dev -- --filter=web\
```\
Then hit `http://localhost:3000`, log in, and your background import flows (`/pricing/price-list/import`, `/pricing/price-list/components/import`) will:\
\
- Enqueue jobs via Redis,\
- Be processed by the worker,\
- Write progress/errors into `ImportJob` rows.\
\
---\
\
## 4. Docker infra\
\
With this setup:\
\
- **No Docker is required for normal local dev.**\
- You can ignore `infra/docker/docker-compose.yml` unless you explicitly need local Postgres/Redis for other experiments.\
- If Docker Desktop auto\uc0\u8209 start is disabled (as you configured), you won\'92t have any hidden port hoggers.\
\
