pkill -f "cloud-sql-proxy" || true         # Cloud SQL proxies\
pkill -f "redis-server" || true            # local redis (if you want to restart it)\
```\
You can trim that list if you want to leave `redis-server` running; e.g. drop the last line if you just want to kill app + proxy, not Redis itself.\
